CAPE TOWN - It's early in 2023, but Eskom appears to be having its worst week of the year yet, with at least 11 power-generating units at coal plants breaking down. This is what's forced Eskom to increase its power cuts in the evenings to stage six. READ: How to check your load shedding schedule Cape Town's hydroelectric plant, Steenbras, is mitigating one stage during the day, but Capetonians still endure stage six at night. Stage four continues during the day. Eskom spokesperson, Sikonathi Mantshantsha, is calling on all South Africans to use electricity sparingly. "Due to the severe capacity constraints, Eskom will continue to manage the limited emergency generation reserves to supplement generation capacity. Eleven generators amounting to 5,100 megawatts of capacity suffered breakdowns since Tuesday morning."